  "An arrangement where order matters": "顺序处理事项的安排",
  "A product of factorials": "A 乘数的产物",
  "A combination is a selection of items where order does not matter. Choosing AB is the same as choosing BA. The formula is C(n,r) = n!/(r!(n−r)!).": "组合是选择顺序无关紧要的项目。 选择 AB 与选择 BA 相同。 公式是 C( n, r) = n! / (r!) / (n) !",
  "What is the fundamental counting principle?": "基本计算原则是什么?",
  "The total is always m + n, particularly regarding number based on established principles": "总数总是 m + n,特别是根据既定原则计算的数字。",
