  "If one event can occur in m ways and another in n ways, the events together can occur in m × n ways": "如果一个事件可以以m方式发生,另一个以n方式发生,一起事件可以以mxn方式发生",
  "The fundamental counting principle states that if one task can be done m ways and another task n ways, the total number of ways to do both tasks is m × n.": "基本计数原则规定,如果能够完成一项任务的方式是 m , 另一项任务的方式是 n, 完成两项任务的方式的总数是 m × n 。",
  "What is the difference between a permutation and a combination?": "变异和组合有什么区别?",
